TY  - JOUR
T1  - Liquidity in Asset Markets With Search Frictions
AU  - Lagos, Ricardo
AU  - Rocheteau, Guillaume
Y1  - 2009/03/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/03/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7250
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 403
EP  - 426
VL  - 77
IS  - 2
KW  - Bid–ask spreads
KW  - trading delays
KW  - liquidity
KW  - search
KW  - trade volume
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA7250
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We develop a search-theoretic model of financial intermediation in an over-the-counter market and study how trading frictions affect the distribution of asset holdings and standard measures of liquidity. A distinctive feature of our theory is that it allows for unrestricted asset holdings, so market participants can accommodate trading frictions by adjusting their asset positions. We show that these individual responses of asset demands constitute a fundamental feature of illiquid markets: they are a key determinant of trade volume, bid?ask spreads, and trading delays?the dimensions of market liquidity that search-based theories seek to explain.
ER  - 

