TY  - JOUR
T1  - Search, Obfuscation, and Price Elasticities on the Internet
AU  - Ellison, Glenn
AU  - Ellison, Sara Fisher
Y1  - 2009/03/01
PY  - 2009
DA  - 2009/03/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA5708
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 427
EP  - 452
VL  - 77
IS  - 2
KW  - Search
KW  - obfuscation
KW  - Internet
KW  - retail
KW  - search engines
KW  - loss leaders
KW  - add-on pricing
KW  - demand elasticities
KW  - frictionless commerce
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA5708
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We examine the competition between a group of Internet retailers who operate in an environment where a price search engine plays a dominant role. We show that for some products in this environment, the easy price search makes demand tremendously price-sensitive. Retailers, though, engage in obfuscation?practices that frustrate consumer search or make it less damaging to firms?resulting in much less price sensitivity on some other products. We discuss several models of obfuscation and examine its effects on demand and markups empirically.
ER  - 

